+  `The dominant treatment pattern was ` + '`treatment_enzalutamide`' + `. It was associated with a large higher response probability overall (${rdLabel(term(adjustedMain, 'treatment_enzalutamide').beta)}, ${pLabel(term(adjustedMain, 'treatment_enzalutamide').p)}; unadjusted ${pp(enza.p1)} on treatment vs ${pp(enza.p0)} off treatment). However, this benefit was almost entirely limited to non-mCRPC patients: in ` + '`mcrpc`' + ` = 0, response was ${pp(enzMcrpc.r10)} with enzalutamide vs ${pp(enzMcrpc.r00)} without it, while in ` + '`mcrpc`' + ` = 1, response was ${pp(enzMcrpc.r11)} with enzalutamide vs ${pp(enzMcrpc.r01)} without it. The ` + '`treatment_enzalutamide:mcrpc`' + ` interaction was strongly negative (${rdLabel(enzMcrpc.beta)}, ${pLabel(enzMcrpc.p)}).`,
