+  '',
+  `Biologically expected precision-treatment patterns were mostly not supported. ` + '`treatment_lu177_psma:psma_high`' + ` was not positive (${rdLabel(luPsma.full_beta)}, ${pLabel(luPsma.full_p)}). ` + '`treatment_pembrolizumab:msi_high`' + ` was near zero (${rdLabel(pembroMsi.full_beta)}, ${pLabel(pembroMsi.full_p)}). ` + '`treatment_olaparib:brca2_mutation`' + ` was borderline significant in the opposite direction (${rdLabel(olaBrca.full_beta)}, ${pLabel(olaBrca.full_p)}), so the expected BRCA2-specific olaparib benefit was refuted in this cohort.`,
+  '',
+  `Exploratory subgroup findings included a positive ` + '`treatment_pembrolizumab:her2_amplification`' + ` interaction (${rdLabel(pembroHer2.full_beta)}, ${pLabel(pembroHer2.full_p)}), a small positive ` + '`treatment_abiraterone:brca2_mutation`' + ` interaction (${rdLabel(abiBrca.full_beta)}, ${pLabel(abiBrca.full_p)}), a negative ` + '`treatment_lu177_psma:visceral_mets`' + ` interaction (${rdLabel(luVisceral.beta)}, ${pLabel(luVisceral.p)}), and a negative ` + '`treatment_olaparib:pleural_effusion`' + ` interaction (${rdLabel(olaPleural.beta)}, ${pLabel(olaPleural.p)}). These should be interpreted as exploratory because many interactions were screened and some positive cells were small, especially pembrolizumab plus HER2 amplification (n=${pembroHer2.n11}).`,
+  '',
+  'Overall, the clearest pattern was not a broad biomarker-matched treatment benefit. Instead, response was dominated by a large enzalutamide-associated response advantage in non-mCRPC, with loss of that advantage in mCRPC and in AR-V7-positive, BRCA2-mutated, and MSI-high subgroups. General disease severity and inflammatory/nutritional markers also tracked response in the expected directions.',
+  '',
+].join('\n');
